 <changelog>
   <release>
    <version>3.0.0beta1</version>
    <date>2004-05-04</date>
    <license>LGPL</license>
    <state>beta</state>
    <notes>Completely recoded version of patTemplate.
Provides an nearly endless amount of new features, see news.txt for
a complete list of changes.
    </notes>
   </release>
   <release>
    <version>3.0.0beta2</version>
    <date>2004-08-22</date>
    <license>LGPL</license>
    <state>beta</state>
    <notes>Changes since 3.0.0beta1:
- improved caching performance by introducing Stat modules
- allowed passing of an array of objects to addObject()
- added addModuleDir() which allows you to store your modules anywhere
- fixed several small bugs
- added Tidy outputfilter
- added BBCode output filter
- variable modifiers now work for globals
- added __toString()
- added loadTemplate()
- added new parameter to clearTemplate() to recursively clear templates
- added limit attribute
- added Expression modifier
- added Translate function (works like IntSmarty)
- added Globalvar function (behaves like &lt;patTemplate:var/&gt;
- added PHPHighlight function
- added Attribute function
- added Call function
- added FTP and HTTP support to File Reader
- added varscope=&quot;__parent&quot;
- added recursive parameter to clearTemplate() and freeTemplate()
- added 'append' parameter to parseIntoVar()
- fixed bug with dot-syntax in simpleCondition templates
    </notes>
   </release>
   <release>
    <version>3.0.0</version>
    <date>2004-11-30</date>
    <license>LGPL</license>
    <state>beta</state>
    <notes>Changes since 3.0.0beta2:
- fixed a notice (bug #65)
- added new system var: PAT_MODULO (request #63)
- fixed behaviour of global variables (bug #66)
- added more possibilities for the addSystemVars attribute (request #64)
- fixed bug with simpleCondition templates and useglobals attribute
- added function aliases
- fixed some warnings and notices (bug #82)
- added support for copyFrom in global variables (gERD)
- fixed bug with default values that got deleted when calling clearTemplate()
- added __empty condition for modulo templates
    </notes>
   </release>
   <release>
    <version>3.0.1</version>
    <date>2005-03-07</date>
    <license>LGPL</license>
    <state>stable</state>
    <notes>Changes since 3.0.0:
- readTemplatesFromInput() now checks, whether any input has been passed (reported by denne)
- fixed notice in addVars()
- improved Dump() for simplecondition templates
- fixed notice in GZip output filter
    </notes>
   </release>
 </changelog>
